  <p>Interpol headquarters issued a Red Notice in mid-April 2026 for Philippine gambling tycoon Charlie "Atong" Ang, the principal suspect in the disappearances of at least 34 sabungeros &mdash; men associated with the country's cockfighting industry, particularly the e-sabong (online cockfighting) sector that operated through 2021 and 2022. The Red Notice elevates the Ang case from a domestic Philippine criminal matter to one that triggers the formal international law-enforcement coordination machinery, while Ang himself reportedly remains in the country.</p>

  <p>Department of Justice Secretary Jesus Crispin Remulla and the Department of the Interior and Local Government's leadership confirmed the Red Notice's release on April 16, 2026. The Philippine government's posture has hardened across the period: DILG has doubled the standing reward for credible information leading to Ang's arrest from PHP 10 million to PHP 20 million.</p>

